Floyd Mayweather has his ex-lover calling him a monster and suing him for plenty of his hard-earned millions.

He has a rapper who used to be his friend and business partner trying to humiliate him with false accusations that he is illiterate.

He has the dangerous duo of Manny Pacquiao and Amir Khan jostling at the head of the queue to be his opponents next year in what he insists will be the last two fill-your-bank-accounts fights of his career.

