Khan, who may be at ringside as he keeps up his pursuit of a fight with Mayweather before the great man retires, expects Maidana to be ‘chasing shadows on Saturday night.’

Britain’s two-time world champion – who awaits confirmation of an opponent for an interim fight in the US on December 6 - holds firm to the belief that ‘my speed is the one element which can give Floyd more problems than he has had of late.’

The waiting game goes on for Khan and Pacquiao, who defends his version of the world welterweight title against Chris Algieri in Macau next month.

The show goes on for Mayweather, circus or not.

